# 2D analog of 3DInclusionFile: read a packing.dat file with `disk` lines
# and instantiate one InterfaceDisk per disk, with the directive's itz/refine
# applied uniformly. Useful when the aggregate placer has produced many
# inclusions that would be tedious to declare inline.
#@output nodes.dat
#@domain 2
#@diam 4.e-3
#@maxiter 1000
#@ranint -1
#@perflag 2 0 0
#@ranflag 1
#@vertex 1 coords 2 -0.005 -0.005
#@vertex 2 coords 2  0.055  0.055
#@rect 1 box 4 0. 0. 0.05 0.05 refine 1.
#@inclusionfile packing.dat itz 0.5e-3 refine 0.5
